function decode(encoded) {
    const n = encoded.length + 1;
    let totalXor = 0;

    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        totalXor ^= i;
    }

    let nonFirstXor = 0;
    for (let i = 1; i < n - 1; i += 2) {
        nonFirstXor ^= encoded[i];
    }

    const perm = new Array(n);
    perm[0] = totalXor ^ nonFirstXor;

    for (let i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        perm[i] = perm[i - 1] ^ encoded[i - 1];
    }

    return perm;
}
```


    1. Calculate the XOR of all numbers from 1 to n, which is called `totalXor`.
2. Calculate the XOR of all even indices of `encoded` array, which is called `nonFirstXor`.
3. The first number in `perm` can be calculated as `totalXor ^ nonFirstXor`.
4. Iterate through the array from 1 to n-1 to fill in the rest of the `perm` array. The value of `perm[i]` is calculated as `perm[i - 1] ^ encoded[i - 1]`.
5. Return the `perm` array.

